<hr />

<h3>Controlling Manhattan</h3>
<ul>
    <li><i>Attacked</i> while in Manhattan <span class="arrow"></span> may flee Manhattan</li>
    <li>Being attacked is the only way to flee Manhattan; a discard card that directly damages you does not count as an attack</li>
    <li>While in Manhattan, heart dice do not heal; but you may still resolve them for other effects, and you can still heal with cards</li>
</ul>

<hr />

<h3>5-6 Players</h3>
<ul>
    <li>2 Manhattan tracks</li>
    <li>Cards / effects that target the monster in Manhattan will affect all monsters in Manhattan</li>
    <li>Manhattan has fewer than 2 monsters during move step <span class="arrow"></span> must move into Manhattan</li>
    <li>Manhattan empty <span class="arrow"></span> move onto 2-4 track</li>
    <li>1 monster in Manhattan <span class="arrow"></span> move onto 5-6 track</li>
    <li>When attacking 2 monsters in Manhattan
        <ul>
            <li>Monster on 2-4 space makes decision to flee or not</li>
            <li>Next, monster on 5-6 space makes the same decision</li>
            <li>2-4 monster flees, but 5-6 monster remains <span class="arrow"></span> move the 5-6 monster onto 2-4 track</li>
            <li>2-4 monster is eliminated <span class="arrow"></span> immediately move the 5-6 monster onto 2-4 track</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Monster(s) eliminated, reducing game size to 4 or less:
        <ul>
            <li>Only 1 monster allowed in Manhattan</li>
            <li>Still 2 monsters in Manhattan <span class="arrow"></span> monster on the 5-6 track must vacate</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ul>

<hr />

<h3>Evolution Cards</h3>
<ul>
    <li><u>At least 3</u> hearts <span class="arrow"></span> draw 2, keep 1</li>
    <li>Cannot trigger twice with 6 hearts</li>
    <li>Being in Manhattan does <u>not</u> prevent resolving hearts (for evolution), only prevents hearts from healing</li>
    <li>Reshuffle deck if empty</li>
    <li>Cards are added hand, hidden from others</li>
    <li>May play cards at any time, even during other players' turns, unless otherwise specified</li>
    <li>When base cards or evolution cards refer to "cards" with no further clarification, it does not apply to evolution cards</li>
</ul>
